Package: fdid
Type: Package
Title: Factorial Difference-in-Differences
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2026-03-01
Authors@R:
    c(person("Rivka", "Lipkovitz", email = "rivkal@mit.edu", role = c("aut")),
      person("Enhan", "Liu", email = "enhan@uchicago.edu", role = c("aut")),
      person("Yiqing", "Xu", , "yiqingxu@stanford.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Implements the factorial difference-in-differences (FDID) framework for panel data settings where all units are exposed to a universal event but vary in a baseline factor G. Provides OLS (with / without interactions), DID, entropy balancing, IPW, and AIPW estimators; supports robust, bootstrap, and jackknife variance; returns dynamic, pre/event/post aggregates and raw means; and includes helpers for data preparation and plotting.
    Methodology follows Xu, Zhao & Ding (2026) <doi:10.1080/01621459.2026.2628343>.
URL: https://github.com/xuyiqing/fdid
